6-03-23 (session 10)\n\n### 9-5-multi-stack-docs-remaining-consumers — create-story (2026-03-23T15:41Z)\n\n- **Ambiguity in epic AC4:** Original epic says verify/env.ts uses `stacks.includes('nodejs')` but actual code calls `detectStack()` directly, not state-based. AC rewritten to reflect actual code path.\n- **ACs already satisfied:** AC2 (getStackLabel arrays) and AC3 (getProjectName multi-file) already implemented from story 9-3. Kept as verify-not-reimplement ACs.\n- **File size risk:** `docs-scaffold.ts` at 229/300 lines, adding multi-stack AGENTS.md generation brings it close to ceiling.\n- **No `readme.test.ts` found:** May need new test file for readme template changes.\n\n### 9-5-multi-stack-docs-remaining-consumers — dev-story (2026-03-23T15:46Z)\n\n- **File size risk:** `docs-scaffold.ts` grew from 229 to ~295 lines — under 300 limit but very close. Future extraction needed.\n- **AC text mismatch:** Story AC mentions `npm ci` but template uses `npm install`. Tests match actual template behavior.\n- **Test ripple effect:** ~15 existing verify-env tests needed updating to add `mockDetectStacks` calls due to detection method change.\n- **AC7 logic difference:** AC specifies `state.stacks?.[0]` but implementation uses `state.stacks?.includes('nodejs')` which is more correct (checks anywhere in array).\n\n### 9-5-multi-stack-docs-remaining-consumers — code-review (2026-03-23T15:51Z)\n\n- **HIGH (fixed):** Single-element `StackDetection[]` bypassed single-stack path — direct callers of `generateAgentsMdContent` got wrong format.\n- **HIGH (fixed):** Empty `StackDetection[]` produced degenerate AGENTS.md with no stack info.\n- **MEDIUM (fixed):** `getInstallCommand('rust')` returned `cargo build` instead of install command.\n- **MEDIUM (fixed):** Zero test coverage for `scaffoldDocs` with `stacks` option (AC5 gap). Added 2 integration tests.\n- **LOW (not fixed):** Duplicated stack-to-label mapping between `getStackLabel()` and `stackDisplayName()`.\n- **LOW (not fixed):** `verify-env.test.ts` still imports/mocks stale `detectStack` (singular).\n- **Coverage:** 97.05% overall, all files above 80% floor. 3153 tests pass.\n\n### 9-5-multi-stack-docs-remaining-consumers — verify (2026-03-23T16:04Z)\n\n- **Time constraint:** Verification not started — session time budget exhausted (27/30 min used, <3 min remaining)\n- **Story left at:** `verifying` — next session will pick it up as Tier C (verifying without proof)\n\n---\n\n# Session Issues Log — 2026-03-23 (session 11, loop 6)\n\n### 9-5-multi-stack-docs-remaining-consumers — verify (2026-03-23T20:08Z)\n\n- **Port conflict:** Shared observability stack was running on ports 8428/9428/16686. Harness-specific docker-compose tried to bind same ports. Required `docker compose -f docker-compose.harness.yml down` to clean up conflicting containers.\n- **Proof parser gap:** AC5 cross-referenced AC1's evidence without its own bash/output code blocks. `codeharness verify` reported 7/8 ACs. Fixed by adding a grep command to AC5 section.\n- **Beads sync failure:** `codeharness sync` failed with `spawnSync bd ENOENT` — beads CLI not installed. Chronic issue across all sessions.\n- **All 8 ACs passed** black-box verification on first attempt.\n- **Epic 9 completed:** All 5 stories done. Retrospective written. Sprint is ALL_DONE (39 stories, 11 epics).\n","numLines":143,"startLine":1,"totalLines":143}}}
