7)\n\n### 9-2-state-schema-migration-multi-stack — create-story (2026-03-23T14:24Z)\n\n- **Ambiguity:** Epic says `stacks: string[]` but `StackName` union type exists from story 9-1. Chose `StackName[]` for type safety.\n- **Missing context:** `InitResult` in `types.ts` may need `stacks` field but epic FR4 doesn't explicitly call it out — implied by scope.\n- **Risk:** `detectStacks()` can return duplicate stack names from multiple directories. `stacks` field needs deduplication.\n- **Observation:** All 8 ACs are cli-verifiable via unit tests — no external dependencies.\n\n### 9-2-state-schema-migration-multi-stack — dev-story (2026-03-23T14:32Z)\n\n- **Pre-existing type errors:** `bridge.test.ts` implicit `any`, `run.test.ts` spread arg type error, `stack.test.ts` missing `endpoint`, `status.test.ts` missing `timeoutSummary`. None from this story.\n- **Workaround:** Used `stacks: ['nodejs'] as StackName[]` instead of `as const` in `stack.test.ts` because readonly tuples aren't assignable to `StackName[]`.\n- **Risk:** `recoverCorruptedState()` recovery path not directly unit-tested for `stacks` field — would need planted `package.json` in temp dir.\n- **Observation:** 19 new tests added, all 3098 tests pass with 0 failures.\n\n### 9-2-state-schema-migration-multi-stack — code-review (2026-03-23T14:36Z)\n\n- **HIGH (fixed):** `init-project.ts` never persisted multi-stacks to state file — only single root stack written. All `detectStacks()` results lost on init.\n- **MEDIUM (fixed):** `writeState()` mutated caller's state object via `state.stack = state.stacks[0]` side effect.\n- **MEDIUM (fixed):** `isValidState()` accepted `stacks: [42, true]` as valid — no element type checking.\n- **MEDIUM (fixed):** `recoverCorruptedState()` produced inconsistent `stack: null` / `stacks: ['nodejs']` state.\n- **LOW (not fixed):** `migrateState()` casts `raw.stack as StackName` without validating against known stack names.\n- **LOW (not fixed):** `recoverCorruptedState()` calls both `detectStack()` and `detectStacks()` — detection runs twice.\n- **LOW (not fixed):** Flaky test in `sprint/__tests__/state.test.ts > writeStateAtomic` — shared file race condition under parallel execution.\n- **Coverage gap:** `init-project.test.ts` has zero assertions on `stacks` field after init. No test for recovery when root null but subdirs have stacks.\n\n---\n\n# Session Issues Log — 2026-03-23 (session 8)\n\n### 9-3-init-orchestrator-per-stack-iteration — create-story (2026-03-23T14:50Z)\n\n- **Stale technical notes:** Original story referenced line numbers from before story 9-2. Rewrote to reflect actual current code state.\n- **Files list correction:** Original story listed `src/commands/init.ts` but missed `docs-scaffold.ts`. `init.ts` doesn't need changes; `docs-scaffold.ts` does for `getStackLabel()`.\n- **Risk:** `path` import missing in init-project.ts — per-stack OTLP loop needs `path.join()` but only `basename` is imported.\n- **Observation:** Story 9-2 already did partial work (added `detectStacks` call and stacks population), reducing scope to per-stack iteration loops.\n\n### 9-3-init-orchestrator-per-stack-iteration — dev-story (2026-03-23T14:55Z)\n\n- **Code quality concern:** Per-stack coverage loop calls `getCoverageTool()` per stack but discards return value — `HarnessState.coverage` only has single `tool` field, not per-stack map. Future addition needed.\n- **Observation:** OTLP per-stack loop assigns `result.otlp` based on matching `detection.stack === stack` (primary stack). Last match wins if duplicates exist.\n- **Observation:** Fallback `if (!result.otlp)` after OTLP loop handles edge case where primary stack isn't in `allStacks`.\n\n### 9-3-init-orchestrator-per-stack-iteration — code-review (2026-03-23T15:02Z)\n\n- **HIGH (fixed):** Per-stack coverage loop was dead code — called `getCoverageTool()` per stack but discarded all return values\n- **HIGH (fixed):** OTLP `result.otlp` matched by stack name only, wrong detection when multiple subdirs share same stack\n- **MEDIUM (fixed):** Double filesystem scan — `detectStack()` calls `detectStacks()` internally, then init called it again\n- **MEDIUM (fixed):** Integration tests mocked `detectStack` but init-project no longer called it after refactor\n- **MEDIUM (fixed):** `state.coverage.tools` assigned without type interface field existing\n- **LOW (not fixed):** `state.coverage.tools` map persisted but no consumer reads it yet\n- **LOW (not fixed):** `detectAppType` only considers primary root stack in multi-stack projects\n\n### 9-3-init-orchestrator-per-stack-iteration — verify (2026-03-23T15:08Z)\n\n- All 4 ACs passed black-box verification\n- Beads sync failed (story file status line not found) — non-blocking\n- Container cleanup succeeded\n- Observability check: VictoriaMetrics stack was down at start, `codeharness stack start` reported shared stack already running (inconsistent)\n\n---\n\n# Session Issues Log — 2026-03-23 (session 9)\n\n### 9-4-multi-stage-dockerfile-generation — create-story (2026-03-23T15:12Z)\n\n- **Workaround:** Overwrote existing skeleton story file (had 3 ACs without verification tags) with full 6-AC story\n- **Risk:** AC4 (validator passes on multi-stage output) depends on dockerfile-validator.ts handling multiple FROM lines — may need validator updates\n- **Risk:** Tech spec says new `generateMultiStackDockerfile()` but epics say update existing function — story opts for backward-compat overload approach\n- **Observation:** All 6 ACs tagged cli-verifiable (unit tests and CLI commands only)\n\n### 9-4-multi-stage-dockerfile-generation — dev-story (2026-03-23T15:16Z)\n\n- **Positive finding:** Validator already handles multi-stage (multiple FROM lines) — no changes needed\n- **Branch coverage 91.17%:** vitest/istanbul artifact with else-if chains — statement/function/line at 100%\n- **No exec-plan/proof docs created:** Story mentions docs/exec-plans/active/ but dev focused on code+tests only\n- **File growth:** dockerfile-template.ts grew from 149 to 220 lines (under 300-line limit)\n\n### 9-4-multi-stage-dockerfile-generation — code-review (2026-03-23T15:21Z)\n\n- **HIGH (fixed):** Missing Showboat proof document — story claimed done but file didn't exist\n- **HIGH (fixed):** Type inconsistency between DockerfileTemplateResult.stacks (required) and InitResult.dockerfile.stacks (optional)\n- **HIGH (fixed):** AGENTS.md stale — didn't reflect new StackDetection[] signature or 5 new helpers\n- **MEDIUM (fixed):** Unknown stacks in multi-stage array produced malformed Dockerfile with no error\n- **MEDIUM (fixed):** Hardcoded python3.12 path in runtimeCopyDirectives — breaks on version change\n- **MEDIUM (fixed):** COPY . . copies entire monorepo into each build stage (wasteful, potential secret leak)\n- **MEDIUM (fixed):** No .dockerignore warning for multi-stage builds\n- **LOW (not fixed):** stacks field naming collision between DockerfileTemplateResult.stacks and InitResult.stacks\n- **LOW (not fixed):** Inconsistent non-root user strategy (node vs nobody)\n- **Coverage:** 97.05% overall, all files above 80% floor. 3131 tests pass.\n\n### 9-4-multi-stage-dockerfile-generation — verify (2026-03-23T15:33Z)\n\n- **Time constraint:** Verification started but session time budget exhausted before verifier could complete\n- **State:** Docker container running, verifier session spawned but still in progress\n- **Story left at:** `verifying` — next session will pick it up as Tier C (verifying without proof)\n\n---\n\n# Session Issues Log — 2026-03-23 (session 10)\n\n### 9-5-multi-stack-docs-remaining-consumers — create-story (2026-03-23T15:41Z)\n\n- **Ambiguity in epic AC4:** Original epic says verify/env.ts uses `stacks.includes('nodejs')` but actual code calls `detectStack()` directly, not state-based. AC rewritten to reflect actual code path.\n- **ACs already satisfied:** AC2 (getStackLabel arrays) and AC3 (getProjectName multi-file) already implemented from story 9-3. Kept as verify-not-reimplement ACs.\n- **File size risk:** `docs-scaffold.ts` at 229/300 lines, adding multi-stack AGENTS.md generation brings it close to ceiling.\n- **No `readme.test.ts` found:** May need new test file for readme template changes.\n\n### 9-5-multi-stack-docs-remaining-consumers — dev-story (2026-03-23T15:46Z)\n\n- **File size risk:** `docs-scaffold.ts` grew from 229 to ~295 lines — under 300 limit but very close. Future extraction needed.\n- **AC text mismatch:** Story AC mentions `npm ci` but template uses `npm install`. Tests match actual template behavior.\n- **Test ripple effect:** ~15 existing verify-env tests needed updating to add `mockDetectStacks` calls due to detection method change.\n- **AC7 logic difference:** AC specifies `state.stacks?.[0]` but implementation uses `state.stacks?.includes('nodejs')` which is more correct (checks anywhere in array).\n\n### 9-5-multi-stack-docs-remaining-consumers — code-review (2026-03-23T15:51Z)\n\n- **HIGH (fixed):** Single-element `StackDetection[]` bypassed single-stack path — direct callers of `generateAgentsMdContent` got wrong format.\n- **HIGH (fixed):** Empty `StackDetection[]` produced degenerate AGENTS.md with no stack info.\n- **MEDIUM (fixed):** `getInstallCommand('rust')` returned `cargo build` instead of install command.\n- **MEDIUM (fixed):** Zero test coverage for `scaffoldDocs` with `stacks` option (AC5 gap). Added 2 integration tests.\n- **LOW (not fixed):** Duplicated stack-to-label mapping between `getStackLabel()` and `stackDisplayName()`.\n- **LOW (not fixed):** `verify-env.test.ts` still imports/mocks stale `detectStack` (singular).\n- **Coverage:** 97.05% overall, all files above 80% floor. 3153 tests pass.\n\n### 9-5-multi-stack-docs-remaining-consumers — verify (2026-03-23T16:04Z)\n\n- **Time constraint:** Verification not started — session time budget exhausted (27/30 min used, <3 min remaining)\n- **Story left at:** `verifying` — next session will pick it up as Tier C (verifying without proof)\n\n---\n\n# Session Issues Log — 2026-03-23 (session 11, loop 6)\n\n### 9-5-multi-stack-docs-remaining-consumers — verify (2026-03-23T20:08Z)\n\n- **Port conflict:** Shared observability stack was running on ports 8428/9428/16686. Harness-specific docker-compose tried to bind same ports. Required `docker compose -f docker-compose.harness.yml down` to clean up conflicting containers.\n- **Proof parser gap:** AC5 cross-referenced AC1's evidence without its own bash/output code blocks. `codeharness verify` reported 7/8 ACs. Fixed by adding a grep command to AC5 section.\n- **Beads sync failure:** `codeharness sync` failed with `spawnSync bd ENOENT` — beads CLI not installed. Chronic issue across all sessions.\n- **All 8 ACs passed** black-box verification on first attempt.\n- **Epic 9 completed:** All 5 stories done. Retrospective written. Sprint is ALL_DONE (39 stories, 11 epics).\n"}}
