{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_01Ek716TeyCWmStiFT1CTQPh","type":"tool_result","content":"     1→# Story 10-1: Create StackProvider Interface and Registry\n     2→\n     3→## Status: backlog\n     4→\n     5→## Story\n     6→\n     7→As a developer,\n     8→I want a StackProvider interface that encapsulates all language-specific behavior,\n     9→So that adding a new language requires only one new file.\n    10→\n    11→## Acceptance Criteria\n    12→\n    13→- [ ] AC1: Given `src/lib/stacks/types.ts` exists, when inspected, then it defines `StackProvider` interface with: `name`, `markers`, `displayName`, `detectAppType()`, `getCoverageTool()`, `detectCoverageConfig()`, `getOtlpPackages()`, `installOtlp()`, `getDockerfileTemplate()`, `getDockerBuildStage()`, `getRuntimeCopyDirectives()`, `getBuildCommands()`, `getTestCommands()`, `getSemgrepLanguages()`, `parseTestOutput()`, `parseCoverageReport()`, `getProjectName()` <!-- verification: cli-verifiable -->\n    14→- [ ] AC2: Given `src/lib/stacks/registry.ts` exists, when `detectStacks()` is called, then it uses the registry's marker list (not hardcoded checks) to detect stacks <!-- verification: cli-verifiable -->\n    15→- [ ] AC3: Given the registry, when `getStackProvider('nodejs')` is called, then it returns the NodejsProvider instance <!-- verification: cli-verifiable -->\n    16→\n    17→## Technical Notes\n    18→\n    19→**Decision 2 (Stack Provider Pattern)** drives this story. The interface must capture every method that currently varies by stack across the codebase.\n    20→\n    21→The `StackProvider` interface definition (from architecture-v3.md):\n    22→\n    23→```typescript\n    24→interface StackProvider {\n    25→  readonly name: StackName;\n    26→  readonly markers: string[];           // e.g., ['package.json']\n    27→  readonly displayName: string;         // e.g., 'Node.js (package.json)'\n    28→\n    29→  detectAppType(dir: string): AppType;\n    30→  getCoverageTool(): CoverageToolName;\n    31→  detectCoverageConfig(dir: string): CoverageToolInfo;\n    32→  getOtlpPackages(): string[];\n    33→  installOtlp(dir: string): OtlpResult;\n    34→  patchStartScript?(dir: string): boolean;\n    35→  getDockerfileTemplate(): string;\n    36→  getDockerBuildStage(): string;\n    37→  getRuntimeCopyDirectives(): string;\n    38→  getBuildCommands(): string[];\n    39→  getTestCommands(): string[];\n    40→  getSemgrepLanguages(): string[];\n    41→  parseTestOutput(output: string): TestCounts;\n    42→  parseCoverageReport(dir: string): number;\n    43→  getProjectName(dir: string): string | null;\n    44→}\n    45→```\n    46→\n    47→The registry uses a `Map<StackName, StackProvider>` and detection iterates marker files via `fs.existsSync()` instead of the current hardcoded conditionals in `src/lib/stack-detect.ts`.\n    48→\n    49→`detectStacks()` currently lives in `src/lib/stack-detect.ts` with direct file checks. Move this logic to `registry.ts` where each registered provider's `markers` array is checked against the project directory.\n    50→\n    51→`StackName` and `AppType` types currently in `src/types/state.ts` should be re-exported from `src/lib/stacks/types.ts`.\n    52→\n    53→## Files to Change\n    54→\n    55→- `src/lib/stacks/types.ts` — Create. Define `StackProvider` interface, `StackName`, `AppType`, `CoverageToolName`, `CoverageToolInfo`, `OtlpResult`, `TestCounts` types\n    56→- `src/lib/stacks/registry.ts` — Create. Implement `Map<StackName, StackProvider>`, `registerProvider()`, `getStackProvider()`, `detectStacks()`, `detectStack()`\n    57→- `src/lib/stacks/index.ts` — Create. Re-export public API: `detectStack`, `detectStacks`, `getStackProvider`, `StackProvider`, `StackName`\n    58→- `src/lib/stack-detect.ts` — Will be replaced by registry.ts (deletion deferred to story 10-5)\n    59→- `src/types/state.ts` — Extract `StackName` and `AppType` to stacks/types.ts, re-export for backward compatibility\n    60→"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":"toolu_01QHWZhKaoHMoBzNcsJTFjiq","session_id":"31f79ff4-68ea-4b44-861b-4091a0c239f5","uuid":"00a06103-3751-4c95-bc3a-0bdf56946e2c","timestamp":"2026-03-24T07:40:04.491Z"}
