{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_01MgasCSahmGNzg12HzDoNgD","type":"tool_result","content":"The file /Users/ivintik/dev/personal/codeharness/_bmad-output/implementation-artifacts/.session-issues.md has been updated successfully."}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"31f79ff4-68ea-4b44-861b-4091a0c239f5","uuid":"9e19a229-62d4-4fc4-a243-e3c8b0d40607","timestamp":"2026-03-24T07:41:46.331Z","tool_use_result":{"filePath":"/Users/ivintik/dev/personal/codeharness/_bmad-output/implementation-artifacts/.session-issues.md","oldString":"# Session Issues Log — 2026-03-24","newString":"# Session Issues Log — 2026-03-24\n\n### 10-1-stackprovider-interface-and-registry — create-story (2026-03-24T07:41Z)\n\n- **Ambiguity:** Epic says StackName/AppType in `src/types/state.ts` but they actually live in `src/lib/stack-detect.ts`. Fixed in story.\n- **Implicit dependency:** AC3 requires stub NodejsProvider but epic puts full impl in story 10-2. Added minimal stub task.\n- **Risk:** Registry `detectStacks()` will coexist with existing `stack-detect.ts` `detectStacks()` during transition.\n- **Observation:** `patchStartScript?` optional method not in AC1 checklist but should be in interface definition.","originalFile":"# Session Issues Log — 2026-03-23 (session 7)\n\n### 9-2-state-schema-migration-multi-stack — create-story (2026-03-23T14:24Z)\n\n- **Ambiguity:** Epic says `stacks: string[]` but `StackName` union type exists from story 9-1. Chose `StackName[]` for type safety.\n- **Missing context:** `InitResult` in `types.ts` may need `stacks` field but epic FR4 doesn't explicitly call it out — implied by scope.\n- **Risk:** `detectStacks()` can return duplicate stack names from multiple directories. `stacks` field needs deduplication.\n- **Observation:** All 8 ACs are cli-verifiable via unit tests — no external dependencies.\n\n### 9-2-state-schema-migration-multi-stack — dev-story (2026-03-23T14:32Z)\n\n- **Pre-existing type errors:** `bridge.test.ts` implicit `any`, `run.test.ts` spread arg type error, `stack.test.ts` missing `endpoint`, `status.test.ts` missing `timeoutSummary`. None from this story.\n- **Workaround:** Used `stacks: ['nodejs'] as StackName[]` instead of `as const` in `stack.test.ts` because readonly tuples aren't assignable to `StackName[]`.\n- **Risk:** `recoverCorruptedState()` recovery path not directly unit-tested for `stacks` field — would need planted `package.json` in temp dir.\n- **Observation:** 19 new tests added, all 3098 tests pass with 0 failures.\n\n### 9-2-state-schema-migration-multi-stack — code-review (2026-03-23T14:36Z)\n\n- **HIGH (fixed):** `init-project.ts` never persisted multi-stacks to state file — only single root stack written. All `detectStacks()` results lost on init.\n- **MEDIUM (fixed):** `writeState()` mutated caller's state object via `state.stack = state.stacks[0]` side effect.\n- **MEDIUM (fixed):** `isValidState()` accepted `stacks: [42, true]` as valid — no element type checking.\n- **MEDIUM (fixed):** `recoverCorruptedState()` produced inconsistent `stack: null` / `stacks: ['nodejs']` state.\n- **LOW (not fixed):** `migrateState()` casts `raw.stack as StackName` without validating against known stack names.\n- **LOW (not fixed):** `recoverCorruptedState()` calls both `detectStack()` and `detectStacks()` — detection runs twice.\n- **LOW (not fixed):** Flaky test in `sprint/__tests__/state.test.ts > writeStateAtomic` — shared file race condition under parallel execution.\n- **Coverage gap:** `init-project.test.ts` has zero assertions on `stacks` field after init. No test for recovery when root null but subdirs have stacks.\n\n---\n\n# Session Issues Log — 2026-03-24\n\n","structuredPatch":[{"oldStart":29,"oldLines":3,"newStart":29,"newLines":10,"lines":[" "," # Session Issues Log — 2026-03-24"," ","+### 10-1-stackprovider-interface-and-registry — create-story (2026-03-24T07:41Z)","+","+- **Ambiguity:** Epic says StackName/AppType in `src/types/state.ts` but they actually live in `src/lib/stack-detect.ts`. Fixed in story.","+- **Implicit dependency:** AC3 requires stub NodejsProvider but epic puts full impl in story 10-2. Added minimal stub task.","+- **Risk:** Registry `detectStacks()` will coexist with existing `stack-detect.ts` `detectStacks()` during transition.","+- **Observation:** `patchStartScript?` optional method not in AC1 checklist but should be in interface definition.","+"]}],"userModified":false,"replaceAll":false}}
