{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_015u1z8VskDopDDfeQdG1yKi","type":"tool_result","content":"     1→# Story 10-1: Create StackProvider Interface and Registry\n     2→\n     3→## Status: backlog\n     4→\n     5→## Story\n     6→\n     7→As a developer,\n     8→I want a StackProvider interface that encapsulates all language-specific behavior,\n     9→So that adding a new language requires only one new file.\n    10→\n    11→## Acceptance Criteria\n    12→\n    13→- [ ] AC1: Given `src/lib/stacks/types.ts` exists, when inspected, then it defines `StackProvider` interface with: `name`, `markers`, `displayName`, `detectAppType()`, `getCoverageTool()`, `detectCoverageConfig()`, `getOtlpPackages()`, `installOtlp()`, `getDockerfileTemplate()`, `getDockerBuildStage()`, `getRuntimeCopyDirectives()`, `getBuildCommands()`, `getTestCommands()`, `getSemgrepLanguages()`, `parseTestOutput()`, `parseCoverageReport()`, `getProjectName()` <!-- verification: cli-verifiable -->\n    14→- [ ] AC2: Given `src/lib/stacks/registry.ts` exists, when `detectStacks()` is called, then it uses the registry's marker list (not hardcoded checks) to detect stacks <!-- verification: cli-verifiable -->\n    15→- [ ] AC3: Given the registry, when `getStackProvider('nodejs')` is called, then it returns the NodejsProvider instance <!-- verification: cli-verifiable -->\n    16→\n    17→## Tasks/Subtasks\n    18→\n    19→- [ ] Task 1: Create `src/lib/stacks/` directory\n    20→- [ ] Task 2: Create `src/lib/stacks/types.ts` — Define `StackProvider` interface with all required methods/properties, plus supporting types: `StackName`, `AppType`, `CoverageToolName`, `CoverageToolInfo`, `OtlpResult`, `TestCounts`\n    21→- [ ] Task 3: Create `src/lib/stacks/registry.ts` — Implement `Map<StackName, StackProvider>`, `registerProvider()`, `getStackProvider()`, `detectStacks()`, `detectStack()` using provider marker arrays instead of hardcoded checks\n    22→- [ ] Task 4: Create a minimal `NodejsProvider` stub in `src/lib/stacks/nodejs.ts` — Implement enough of `StackProvider` to satisfy AC3 (returns correct `name`, `markers`, `displayName`; other methods can throw `'not yet implemented'`)\n    23→- [ ] Task 5: Create `src/lib/stacks/index.ts` — Re-export public API: `detectStack`, `detectStacks`, `getStackProvider`, `registerProvider`, `StackProvider`, `StackName`, `AppType`\n    24→- [ ] Task 6: Update `src/lib/stack-detect.ts` — Re-export `StackName` and `AppType` from `src/lib/stacks/types.ts` for backward compatibility (existing imports continue to work)\n    25→- [ ] Task 7: Register `NodejsProvider` in registry (auto-registration in module initialization or explicit call)\n    26→- [ ] Task 8: Add tests in `src/lib/__tests__/stacks/` — Cover: interface shape validation, registry `getStackProvider()`, registry `detectStacks()` using markers, backward compatibility of re-exports\n    27→\n    28→## Technical Notes\n    29→\n    30→**Decision 2 (Stack Provider Pattern)** drives this story. The interface must capture every method that currently varies by stack across the codebase.\n    31→\n    32→The `StackProvider` interface definition (from architecture-v3.md):\n    33→\n    34→```typescript\n    35→interface StackProvider {\n    36→  readonly name: StackName;\n    37→  readonly markers: string[];           // e.g., ['package.json']\n    38→  readonly displayName: string;         // e.g., 'Node.js (package.json)'\n    39→\n    40→  detectAppType(dir: string): AppType;\n    41→  getCoverageTool(): CoverageToolName;\n    42→  detectCoverageConfig(dir: string): CoverageToolInfo;\n    43→  getOtlpPackages(): string[];\n    44→  installOtlp(dir: string): OtlpResult;\n    45→  patchStartScript?(dir: string): boolean;\n    46→  getDockerfileTemplate(): string;\n    47→  getDockerBuildStage(): string;\n    48→  getRuntimeCopyDirectives(): string;\n    49→  getBuildCommands(): string[];\n    50→  getTestCommands(): string[];\n    51→  getSemgrepLanguages(): string[];\n    52→  parseTestOutput(output: string): TestCounts;\n    53→  parseCoverageReport(dir: string): number;\n    54→  getProjectName(dir: string): string | null;\n    55→}\n    56→```\n    57→\n    58→The registry uses a `Map<StackName, StackProvider>` and detection iterates marker files via `fs.existsSync()` instead of the current hardcoded conditionals in `src/lib/stack-detect.ts`.\n    59→\n    60→`detectStacks()` currently lives in `src/lib/stack-detect.ts` with direct file checks. Move this logic to `registry.ts` where each registered provider's `markers` array is checked against the project directory.\n    61→\n    62→`StackName` and `AppType` types currently live in `src/lib/stack-detect.ts` (not `src/types/state.ts`). They should be moved to `src/lib/stacks/types.ts` and re-exported from `src/lib/stack-detect.ts` for backward compatibility.\n    63→\n    64→### Important: Stub vs Full Provider\n    65→\n    66→AC3 requires `getStackProvider('nodejs')` to return a NodejsProvider instance. This means a minimal NodejsProvider must be created in this story (at least registered with correct `name`, `markers`, `displayName`). Full method implementations happen in story 10-2.\n    67→\n    68→### Backward Compatibility\n    69→\n    70→`src/lib/stack-detect.ts` must continue exporting `StackName`, `AppType`, `detectStack()`, `detectStacks()`, `detectAppType()`, and `StackDetection` so existing consumers don't break. It can re-export from the new modules or keep its own implementation until story 10-5 migrates consumers.\n    71→\n    72→## Files to Change\n    73→\n    74→- `src/lib/stacks/types.ts` — Create. Define `StackProvider` interface, `StackName`, `AppType`, `CoverageToolName`, `CoverageToolInfo`, `OtlpResult`, `TestCounts` types\n    75→- `src/lib/stacks/registry.ts` — Create. Implement `Map<StackName, StackProvider>`, `registerProvider()`, `getStackProvider()`, `detectStacks()`, `detectStack()`\n    76→- `src/lib/stacks/nodejs.ts` — Create. Minimal `NodejsProvider` stub implementing `StackProvider` (full implementation in story 10-2)\n    77→- `src/lib/stacks/index.ts` — Create. Re-export public API: `detectStack`, `detectStacks`, `getStackProvider`, `registerProvider`, `StackProvider`, `StackName`\n    78→- `src/lib/stack-detect.ts` — Re-export `StackName` and `AppType` from stacks/types.ts for backward compatibility (deletion deferred to story 10-5)\n    79→- `src/lib/__tests__/stacks/` — Create. Tests for types, registry, and detection\n    80→"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"31f79ff4-68ea-4b44-861b-4091a0c239f5","uuid":"37ef00c3-231c-4f8b-becb-8290946e2640","timestamp":"2026-03-24T07:41:50.997Z","tool_use_result":{"type":"text","file":{"filePath":"/Users/ivintik/dev/personal/codeharness/_bmad-output/implementation-artifacts/10-1-stackprovider-interface-and-registry.md","content":"# Story 10-1: Create StackProvider Interface and Registry\n\n## Status: backlog\n\n## Story\n\nAs a developer,\nI want a StackProvider interface that encapsulates all language-specific behavior,\nSo that adding a new language requires only one new file.\n\n## Acceptance Criteria\n\n- [ ] AC1: Given `src/lib/stacks/types.ts` exists, when inspected, then it defines `StackProvider` interface with: `name`, `markers`, `displayName`, `detectAppType()`, `getCoverageTool()`, `detectCoverageConfig()`, `getOtlpPackages()`, `installOtlp()`, `getDockerfileTemplate()`, `getDockerBuildStage()`, `getRuntimeCopyDirectives()`, `getBuildCommands()`, `getTestCommands()`, `getSemgrepLanguages()`, `parseTestOutput()`, `parseCoverageReport()`, `getProjectName()` <!-- verification: cli-verifiable -->\n- [ ] AC2: Given `src/lib/stacks/registry.ts` exists, when `detectStacks()` is called, then it uses the registry's marker list (not hardcoded checks) to detect stacks <!-- verification: cli-verifiable -->\n- [ ] AC3: Given the registry, when `getStackProvider('nodejs')` is called, then it returns the NodejsProvider instance <!-- verification: cli-verifiable -->\n\n## Tasks/Subtasks\n\n- [ ] Task 1: Create `src/lib/stacks/` directory\n- [ ] Task 2: Create `src/lib/stacks/types.ts` — Define `StackProvider` interface with all required methods/properties, plus supporting types: `StackName`, `AppType`, `CoverageToolName`, `CoverageToolInfo`, `OtlpResult`, `TestCounts`\n- [ ] Task 3: Create `src/lib/stacks/registry.ts` — Implement `Map<StackName, StackProvider>`, `registerProvider()`, `getStackProvider()`, `detectStacks()`, `detectStack()` using provider marker arrays instead of hardcoded checks\n- [ ] Task 4: Create a minimal `NodejsProvider` stub in `src/lib/stacks/nodejs.ts` — Implement enough of `StackProvider` to satisfy AC3 (returns correct `name`, `markers`, `displayName`; other methods can throw `'not yet implemented'`)\n- [ ] Task 5: Create `src/lib/stacks/index.ts` — Re-export public API: `detectStack`, `detectStacks`, `getStackProvider`, `registerProvider`, `StackProvider`, `StackName`, `AppType`\n- [ ] Task 6: Update `src/lib/stack-detect.ts` — Re-export `StackName` and `AppType` from `src/lib/stacks/types.ts` for backward compatibility (existing imports continue to work)\n- [ ] Task 7: Register `NodejsProvider` in registry (auto-registration in module initialization or explicit call)\n- [ ] Task 8: Add tests in `src/lib/__tests__/stacks/` — Cover: interface shape validation, registry `getStackProvider()`, registry `detectStacks()` using markers, backward compatibility of re-exports\n\n## Technical Notes\n\n**Decision 2 (Stack Provider Pattern)** drives this story. The interface must capture every method that currently varies by stack across the codebase.\n\nThe `StackProvider` interface definition (from architecture-v3.md):\n\n```typescript\ninterface StackProvider {\n  readonly name: StackName;\n  readonly markers: string[];           // e.g., ['package.json']\n  readonly displayName: string;         // e.g., 'Node.js (package.json)'\n\n  detectAppType(dir: string): AppType;\n  getCoverageTool(): CoverageToolName;\n  detectCoverageConfig(dir: string): CoverageToolInfo;\n  getOtlpPackages(): string[];\n  installOtlp(dir: string): OtlpResult;\n  patchStartScript?(dir: string): boolean;\n  getDockerfileTemplate(): string;\n  getDockerBuildStage(): string;\n  getRuntimeCopyDirectives(): string;\n  getBuildCommands(): string[];\n  getTestCommands(): string[];\n  getSemgrepLanguages(): string[];\n  parseTestOutput(output: string): TestCounts;\n  parseCoverageReport(dir: string): number;\n  getProjectName(dir: string): string | null;\n}\n```\n\nThe registry uses a `Map<StackName, StackProvider>` and detection iterates marker files via `fs.existsSync()` instead of the current hardcoded conditionals in `src/lib/stack-detect.ts`.\n\n`detectStacks()` currently lives in `src/lib/stack-detect.ts` with direct file checks. Move this logic to `registry.ts` where each registered provider's `markers` array is checked against the project directory.\n\n`StackName` and `AppType` types currently live in `src/lib/stack-detect.ts` (not `src/types/state.ts`). They should be moved to `src/lib/stacks/types.ts` and re-exported from `src/lib/stack-detect.ts` for backward compatibility.\n\n### Important: Stub vs Full Provider\n\nAC3 requires `getStackProvider('nodejs')` to return a NodejsProvider instance. This means a minimal NodejsProvider must be created in this story (at least registered with correct `name`, `markers`, `displayName`). Full method implementations happen in story 10-2.\n\n### Backward Compatibility\n\n`src/lib/stack-detect.ts` must continue exporting `StackName`, `AppType`, `detectStack()`, `detectStacks()`, `detectAppType()`, and `StackDetection` so existing consumers don't break. It can re-export from the new modules or keep its own implementation until story 10-5 migrates consumers.\n\n## Files to Change\n\n- `src/lib/stacks/types.ts` — Create. Define `StackProvider` interface, `StackName`, `AppType`, `CoverageToolName`, `CoverageToolInfo`, `OtlpResult`, `TestCounts` types\n- `src/lib/stacks/registry.ts` — Create. Implement `Map<StackName, StackProvider>`, `registerProvider()`, `getStackProvider()`, `detectStacks()`, `detectStack()`\n- `src/lib/stacks/nodejs.ts` — Create. Minimal `NodejsProvider` stub implementing `StackProvider` (full implementation in story 10-2)\n- `src/lib/stacks/index.ts` — Create. Re-export public API: `detectStack`, `detectStacks`, `getStackProvider`, `registerProvider`, `StackProvider`, `StackName`\n- `src/lib/stack-detect.ts` — Re-export `StackName` and `AppType` from stacks/types.ts for backward compatibility (deletion deferred to story 10-5)\n- `src/lib/__tests__/stacks/` — Create. Tests for types, registry, and detection\n","numLines":80,"startLine":1,"totalLines":80}}}
