{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_019iMKAnmf2eLQ7swhAqkwtG","type":"tool_result","content":[{"type":"text","text":"All done. Here is the summary:\n\n## What was done\n\n**Story 10-1: Create StackProvider Interface and Registry** — all 8 tasks completed, all 3 ACs satisfied, story marked for review.\n\n### Files created\n- `/Users/ivintik/dev/personal/codeharness/src/lib/stacks/types.ts` — `StackProvider` interface with all 16 methods/properties, plus `StackName`, `AppType`, `CoverageToolName`, `CoverageToolInfo`, `OtlpResult`, `TestCounts` types\n- `/Users/ivintik/dev/personal/codeharness/src/lib/stacks/registry.ts` — `Map<StackName, StackProvider>` registry with `registerProvider()`, `getStackProvider()`, `detectStacks()`, `detectStack()` using marker-based detection, priority ordering, SKIP_DIRS, and `_resetRegistry()` for testing\n- `/Users/ivintik/dev/personal/codeharness/src/lib/stacks/nodejs.ts` — `NodejsProvider` class stub with correct `name`, `markers`, `displayName`; all other methods throw \"not yet implemented\"\n- `/Users/ivintik/dev/personal/codeharness/src/lib/stacks/index.ts` — Public API re-exports + auto-registration of `NodejsProvider`\n- `/Users/ivintik/dev/personal/codeharness/src/lib/__tests__/stacks/types.test.ts` — 9 tests: interface shape validation, type assignability, optional `patchStartScript`\n- `/Users/ivintik/dev/personal/codeharness/src/lib/__tests__/stacks/registry.test.ts` — 18 tests: register/get, AC3 NodejsProvider instance check, marker-based detection, priority ordering, skip dirs, subdirectory scanning, compat wrapper\n- `/Users/ivintik/dev/personal/codeharness/src/lib/__tests__/stacks/backward-compat.test.ts` — 3 tests: verify `stack-detect.ts` re-exports still work\n\n### Files modified\n- `/Users/ivintik/dev/personal/codeharness/src/lib/stack-detect.ts` — Replaced inline `StackName` and `AppType` type definitions with re-exports from `stacks/types.ts`\n- `/Users/ivintik/dev/personal/codeharness/_bmad-output/implementation-artifacts/10-1-stackprovider-interface-and-registry.md` — Status changed to `review`, all ACs and tasks checked off\n\n### Test results\n- 30 new tests pass (3 test files)\n- 79 existing `stack-detect.test.ts` tests pass (backward compatibility confirmed)\n- Zero TypeScript errors in new files\n\n## Session Issues\n\n- **Observation:** The `stack-detect.ts` module still has its own `detectStacks()` / `detectStack()` / `detectAppType()` implementations with hardcoded marker checks. The new `registry.ts` has a parallel marker-based implementation. Existing consumers still import from `stack-detect.ts`. Story 10-5 is expected to migrate consumers to the new registry, at which point the old implementations can be removed. Until then, there are two parallel detection codepaths.\n- **Observation:** Pre-existing TypeScript compilation errors exist in ~10 other test files (bridge, run, stack, status, teardown, deps, sync). These are unrelated to this story.\n- **Code quality note:** The registry uses module-level `Map` state, which means import order matters. Auto-registration in `index.ts` ensures `NodejsProvider` is registered whenever the stacks module is imported, but consumers importing directly from `registry.ts` won't get auto-registration. This is acceptable for now since `index.ts` is the public API entry point."},{"type":"text","text":"agentId: a7bc1b893b1fa1db5 (use SendMessage with to: 'a7bc1b893b1fa1db5' to continue this agent)\n<usage>total_tokens: 46885\ntool_uses: 27\nduration_ms: 187672</usage>"}]}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"31f79ff4-68ea-4b44-861b-4091a0c239f5","uuid":"6bbd1ab4-395e-4735-b8de-3550485be322","timestamp":"2026-03-24T07:45:13.763Z","tool_use_result":{"status":"completed","prompt":"Run /bmad-dev-story for the story at _bmad-output/implementation-artifacts/10-1-stackprovider-interface-and-registry.md — implement all tasks, write tests, and mark the story for review. Do NOT ask the user any questions — proceed autonomously through all tasks until complete. Do NOT run git commit. Do NOT run git add. Do NOT modify sprint-status.yaml.\n\nMANDATORY — End your response with a `## Session Issues` section listing:\n- Problems encountered (build failures, test failures, unclear task specs, missing APIs)\n- Workarounds applied (anything hacky, copied patterns that felt wrong, TODOs left behind)\n- Code quality concerns (areas that need refactoring, edge cases not handled, tech debt added)\n- Observations (unexpected complexity, architectural mismatches, dependency issues)\nIf nothing to report, write `## Session Issues\\n\\nNone.`","agentId":"a7bc1b893b1fa1db5","content":[{"type":"text","text":"All done. Here is the summary:\n\n## What was done\n\n**Story 10-1: Create StackProvider Interface and Registry** — all 8 tasks completed, all 3 ACs satisfied, story marked for review.\n\n### Files created\n- `/Users/ivintik/dev/personal/codeharness/src/lib/stacks/types.ts` — `StackProvider` interface with all 16 methods/properties, plus `StackName`, `AppType`, `CoverageToolName`, `CoverageToolInfo`, `OtlpResult`, `TestCounts` types\n- `/Users/ivintik/dev/personal/codeharness/src/lib/stacks/registry.ts` — `Map<StackName, StackProvider>` registry with `registerProvider()`, `getStackProvider()`, `detectStacks()`, `detectStack()` using marker-based detection, priority ordering, SKIP_DIRS, and `_resetRegistry()` for testing\n- `/Users/ivintik/dev/personal/codeharness/src/lib/stacks/nodejs.ts` — `NodejsProvider` class stub with correct `name`, `markers`, `displayName`; all other methods throw \"not yet implemented\"\n- `/Users/ivintik/dev/personal/codeharness/src/lib/stacks/index.ts` — Public API re-exports + auto-registration of `NodejsProvider`\n- `/Users/ivintik/dev/personal/codeharness/src/lib/__tests__/stacks/types.test.ts` — 9 tests: interface shape validation, type assignability, optional `patchStartScript`\n- `/Users/ivintik/dev/personal/codeharness/src/lib/__tests__/stacks/registry.test.ts` — 18 tests: register/get, AC3 NodejsProvider instance check, marker-based detection, priority ordering, skip dirs, subdirectory scanning, compat wrapper\n- `/Users/ivintik/dev/personal/codeharness/src/lib/__tests__/stacks/backward-compat.test.ts` — 3 tests: verify `stack-detect.ts` re-exports still work\n\n### Files modified\n- `/Users/ivintik/dev/personal/codeharness/src/lib/stack-detect.ts` — Replaced inline `StackName` and `AppType` type definitions with re-exports from `stacks/types.ts`\n- `/Users/ivintik/dev/personal/codeharness/_bmad-output/implementation-artifacts/10-1-stackprovider-interface-and-registry.md` — Status changed to `review`, all ACs and tasks checked off\n\n### Test results\n- 30 new tests pass (3 test files)\n- 79 existing `stack-detect.test.ts` tests pass (backward compatibility confirmed)\n- Zero TypeScript errors in new files\n\n## Session Issues\n\n- **Observation:** The `stack-detect.ts` module still has its own `detectStacks()` / `detectStack()` / `detectAppType()` implementations with hardcoded marker checks. The new `registry.ts` has a parallel marker-based implementation. Existing consumers still import from `stack-detect.ts`. Story 10-5 is expected to migrate consumers to the new registry, at which point the old implementations can be removed. Until then, there are two parallel detection codepaths.\n- **Observation:** Pre-existing TypeScript compilation errors exist in ~10 other test files (bridge, run, stack, status, teardown, deps, sync). These are unrelated to this story.\n- **Code quality note:** The registry uses module-level `Map` state, which means import order matters. Auto-registration in `index.ts` ensures `NodejsProvider` is registered whenever the stacks module is imported, but consumers importing directly from `registry.ts` won't get auto-registration. This is acceptable for now since `index.ts` is the public API entry point."}],"totalDurationMs":187672,"totalTokens":46885,"totalToolUseCount":27,"usa