{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_01NBw9a8P5guFFtTFy7if2e9","type":"tool_result","content":[{"type":"text","text":"---\n\n## Review Summary\n\n**Story:** 10-1-stackprovider-interface-and-registry\n**Status:** Updated to `verifying`\n**Issues Found:** 2 High, 3 Medium, 1 Low\n\n### HIGH issues (fixed)\n\n1. **`src/lib/stacks/index.ts` at 0% coverage** -- Barrel file with auto-registration side effect was never exercised by tests. Fixed by adding `/Users/ivintik/dev/personal/codeharness/src/lib/__tests__/stacks/index.test.ts` that imports through the barrel and validates auto-registration.\n\n2. **`src/lib/stacks/nodejs.ts` at 17.64% coverage** -- Only 3 readonly properties tested; 13 stub methods never called. Fixed by adding `/Users/ivintik/dev/personal/codeharness/src/lib/__tests__/stacks/nodejs.test.ts` that calls every stub method and asserts the `not yet implemented` error.\n\n### MEDIUM issues (fixed)\n\n3. **Bare `catch {}` in `registry.ts` line 73** -- `readdirSync` errors silently swallowed with no comment. Fixed by adding `_err: unknown` binding and an explanatory comment.\n\n### MEDIUM issues (not fixed -- deferred per story scope)\n\n4. **`StackDetection` type duplicated** -- Defined independently in both `registry.ts` and `stack-detect.ts` with identical shape. Should be a single source of truth. Deferred to story 10-5 (migration story).\n\n5. **`stack-detect.ts` still has independent detection logic** -- Not a re-export from the new registry. Acceptable per story notes (migration in 10-5), but creates a code path divergence risk.\n\n### Coverage Results (post-fix)\n\n- Overall: **97.06%** (target: 90%) -- PASS\n- Per-file floor: **All 127 files above 80%** -- PASS\n\n### AC Validation\n\n- AC1 (StackProvider interface in types.ts): **IMPLEMENTED** -- All 15 required methods/properties present, plus supporting types.\n- AC2 (detectStacks uses registry markers): **IMPLEMENTED** -- `registry.ts` iterates registered provider marker arrays.\n- AC3 (getStackProvider('nodejs') returns NodejsProvider): **IMPLEMENTED** -- Auto-registered via barrel import.\n\n### Task Audit\n\nAll 8 tasks marked `[x]` verified as implemented against the codebase.\n\n## Session Issues\n\n**Bugs found:**\n- None (no functional bugs)\n\n**Code quality issues found but NOT fixed (LOW):**\n- `_resetRegistry` exported from public barrel `index.ts` -- test-only utility leaking into public API. Mitigated by `_` prefix and `@internal` JSDoc.\n\n**Coverage gaps:**\n- `registry.ts` error path in `readdirSync` catch block not tested (would require mocking `readdirSync` to throw on a valid-looking path). Edge case, not blocking.\n- No integration test verifying that `stacks/index.ts` barrel auto-registration survives tree-shaking or bundling scenarios.\n\n**Architecture concerns:**\n- `StackDetection` type duplication between `registry.ts` and `stack-detect.ts` creates divergence risk. Must be resolved in story 10-5.\n- Two parallel detection codepaths (`stack-detect.ts` hardcoded markers vs `registry.ts` provider-based) will coexist until 10-5 completes. Consumers using `stack-detect.ts` won't benefit from new providers registered with the registry.\n\n**Items sent back for re-development:**\n- None. All HIGH and MEDIUM fixable issues resolved. Story moved to `verifying`."},{"type":"text","text":"agentId: aefff7a86b3e3249e (use SendMessage with to: 'aefff7a86b3e3249e' to continue this agent)\n<usage>total_tokens: 45935\ntool_uses: 37\nduration_ms: 193137</usage>"}]}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"31f79ff4-68ea-4b44-861b-4091a0c239f5","uuid":"08dfdd03-fcc9-49e4-a83c-c66a60c4ed81","timestamp":"2026-03-24T07:49:01.428Z","tool_use_result":{"status":"completed","prompt":"Run /bmad-code-review for the story at _bmad-output/implementation-artifacts/10-1-stackprovider-interface-and-registry.md — perform adversarial review, fix all HIGH and MEDIUM issues found. After fixing, run `codeharness coverage --min-file